			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class='snap_preview'><br /><p>I have been gone, better yet have been growing.  This week has been a week of reflection for me.  I know I have a lot to say and sometimes when I talk it is also a personal acknowledgment to myself.  Bring upon controversy so I have to grow.</p>
<p>So that is what has happened.  I needed time to think, time to plan, time to reflect.</p>
<p>So I picked up my old journal.  I bought it in 1998 when on a senior field trip with my best friends &#8212; mind you I was not a senior at the time.  A little journal with a leopard design.  That book has held the secrets of my past for 10 years.  I pulled it out to write the blog about my grandmother&#8217;s death.  Tonight I read it cover to cover.  Then I added a few new additions that were way past due.</p>
<p>Dated 6-1-99 (notice a little less than 6 months after i was raped)</p>
<p>&#8220;I&#8217;m reading a book called telling a memoir of rape and recovery.  It says to say a man raped me instead of I was raped.  It&#8217;s true how the emotions of it can&#8217;t exactly be explained, the sleepless nights, fear of every shadow not to mention the dreadful aids tests.  This has been a very difficult year first my grandmother&#8217;s death then &#8216;the rape.&#8217;  I did an article for Irvine World News, it was such a great feeling.  I am having a hard time sleeping lately so I bought another angel book.  This one is really good it also talks about spirit guides.  I haven&#8217;t gotten there yet oh well.  My mom doesn&#8217;t understand my fears about it, and I can&#8217;t seem to explain it to her effectively this will be a long process of healing but <strong>I will</strong> get better it will just take a while.</p>
<p>Love, Me&#8221;</p>
<p>When I read this I had to add a new entry &#8211;</p>
<p>&#8220;And you did! 12/4/08&#8243;</p>
<p>Not sure my bottom line here.  I had to grow, I had to learn.  Writing comes natural and yet it must be organic for me.  It is 3 in the morning and I felt compelled, so I sit here to write.  </p>
<p>I guess it is all about sharing.  What I wrote 10 years ago I never thought I would share.  I write what I feel and think in hope that it causes another to think.  Another to question, and another to challenge.  Everything that we are, believe and think is a result of our socialization.  I constantly challenge you so that I may challenge myself.  As human beings it is our right to question and our obligation.  Why be given free will, to only succumb to everything that has already been previously indoctrinated into us?  </p>
<p>Go take a look at yourself 10 years ago and ask why you have grown.  I had to.  Last week I spent alone in my house &#8212; that was inconceivable 10 years ago.  Life happens it is all about how we perceive it.  This is not new, it has been delivered from many messengers so when will you choose to hear it.  </p>
<p>Journal entry 12/5/08</p>
<p>I&#8217;m 27 and have had so many lovers and less loves.  I learn, I grow.  I forgot to write for a long time, and yet it was all I ever used to do.  It was  1998 when I bought this book.  I was 16.  Almost 10 years &#8212; wait 10+ years ago &#8212; my I have grown.  Sometimes I still act like the lost child.  I&#8217;m not lost I&#8217;ve always known where I was headed.  Don&#8217;t you wish we could go back and tell our past selves it would be ok?  Well it is and better.  I still push I am still challenged &#8212; but it is all ok.  I am alive AND I have made a difference &#8212; I have started building a legacy.  Reading through this I relive my life.  I feel like I am reading the go ask alice book.  I have lived I have loved I have learned, its not about the past its about the future.  Dear children NEVER judge yourselves live, love, grow that is all there ever will be xoxo Chimine</p>
<p>P.S. I was referring to my future children</p>
<p>Thank You</p>
<p>Chimine</p>
